comment: 1:28 Nah, I disagree.  I don't believe that Johnny Depp ever instigated any sort of violence in any relationship.  If that was his nature in any way, somebody would've agreed with Amber.  Nobody has.  That being said, I would guess that Johnny's not an easy guy, either.  He's not a saint, for sure & being the type of creative that he is, this is not an easy personality for many women to live with.  Artists are complex people & Johnny has never hidden his "weird" but I think women have a perception of him that differs from the reality.  Listening to the "argument" tapes, it would seem that Amber couldn't handle Johnny's passivity & lack of willingness to fight with her.  She wanted to get him riled up cuz... "Those who anger you, control you" & she wanted to control him.  In essence, she couldn't handle his level of self-control.  She couldn't make him lose it on her & it incensed her to the point where she took it to the place of violence at the onset of any argument.  If you understand the mentality of what Amber is (a narcissistic abuser) then you know that these types of people use the level of force necessary to control their victim.  At the start it's subtle manipulation - it's emotional & mental.  It generally escalates to the physical thing as the victim starts to catch onto the game & resist being controlled.  Johnny, though, I think was probably somewhat unaware of the game, even as it was escalating - having been conditioned by a lot of childhood trauma & the manipulation phase never gave Amber the "control fix" she was after, so she escalated very quickly to this consistent violence while Johnny chose to remove himself from the argument rather than engage.  I would guess that started happening after the first incident of Amber assaulting him, physically.  Once he knew that she would breech that trust, he made it a point of practice to leave the arena & let Amber fume & scream at her reflection instead of at him.  Wise on his part because now...he's innocent & she's getting what's coming to her for a very long time...long before she even met Johnny Depp.

comment:
Always good and balanced content and I have yet to see anything in any of your videos that deserves any kind of negativity from the likes of Youtube.
"...he is destined to loose."
What!?!
He has evidence that the Sun libelled him - he should absolutely go after this awful rag! (I'm a UK resident by the way)
This would seem to be an example of "you are a man and so nobody will listen to you" along with "we don't like you may besmirch one of our favorite women".
From a purely crass point of view his career is already done, that cannot be repaired. But he has his name to defend and so his children too!
Such cases here in the UK have generally gone with the plaintiff with less evidence. 
Will Amber Heard try to drag him through the muck? Absolutely! But us Brits still have a sense of fair play and have no time for liars... especially liars who use their "in built" advantages to pursue those lies.
There's also a thing called precedent. Should a UK court find against the Sun, and I expect so, it's going to be very hard for anyone to badmouth JD in future and indeed may be helpful to him with any legal proceedings he may wish to take in the US.
